.<img width="1024" height="683" class="wp-image-1802404" style="width: 700px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Oborevwori-8.jpg" alt="Oborevwori" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Oborevwori-8.jpg?width=1024&amp;auto_optimize=medium 1024w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Oborevwori-8-300x200.jpg?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Oborevwori-8-768x512.jpg?width=768&amp;auto_optimize=medium 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /> …Edebvie, Angozi disappear from aspirants’ canopy  By Festus Ahon & Paul Olayemi, ASABA SPEAKER of the Delta State House of Assembly, Rt Hon Sheriff Oborevwori is in the early lead of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP primary election.  In the sorting and counting which is being done in the full glare of the cameras, Journalists, security agents, and officials of the Independent Electoral Commission, INEC, Oborevwori has scored 285 votes in the three out of the six ballot boxes so far sorted.  Meanwhile, Chief David Edevbie and Mr. Braduce Angozi left the aspirants’ canopy before the end of the election.